<emphasis id="B90F4C48502EFFD3FF63F882FEC73904" bold="true" box="[151,276,1797,1821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502EFFD3FEE8F882FD8D3904" authority="Jimi &amp; Chen &amp; Fujiwara, 2022" authorityName="Jimi &amp; Chen &amp; Fujiwara" authorityYear="2022" box="[284,606,1797,1821]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sagamiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502EFFD3FEE8F882FD8D3904" box="[284,606,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Branchinotogluma sagamiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502EFFD3FD91F882FD643904" bold="true" box="[613,695,1797,1821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23CF133502EFFD3FD91F882FD643904" box="[613,695,1797,1821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502EFFD3FF63F8F6FD713990" blockId="6.[151,1437,1797,1929]" box="[151,674,1905,1929]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502FFFD2FF33FF11FB663DBD" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502FFFD2FF33FF11FA5A3C00" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502FFFD2FF33FF11FE823EA9" bold="true" box="[199,337,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Description</emphasis>
: Male 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502FFFD2FE57FF11FE363EA8" box="[419,485,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502FFFD2FDD9FF11FDBC3EA8" box="[557,623,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
wide (with parapodia, without chaetae), with 20 segments, flat (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FABDFF11FA5C3EA9" box="[1353,1423,150,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Living colour purple-red. Body without dorsal tubercles. Ten pairs of elytra on segments 2, 4, 5, 7, and alternating segments to 19. Elytra transparent, without fringing papillae at outer margins, without microtubercles and macrotubercles. Bilobed prostomium pinkish in live specimens (whitish in ethanol) bilobed, with distinct anterior lobes; anterior lobes cylindrical, without conical frontal filaments (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FCB2FEA1FC703F59" box="[838,931,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FC44FEA1FC053F58" box="[944,982,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6A</figureCitation>
). Median antenna with short cylindrical ceratophore, inserted at anterior notch of prostomium (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FCF4FECDFC8E3F7D" box="[768,861,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FC9DFECDFC5C3F7C" box="[873,911,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6A</figureCitation>
); style 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502FFFD2FC14FECDFBEA3F7C" box="[992,1081,330,357]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, not papillate, thin and tapered. Lateral antennae absent. Eyes absent. Palps as long as ventral tentacular cirri (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FBE1FEE9FBA13F91" box="[1045,1138,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FB8BFEE9FB763F90" box="[1151,1189,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6A</figureCitation>
), whitish, smooth, tapered in tips. Dorsal and ventral tentacular cirri with tentaculophores lateral to prostomium. Dorsal tentacular cirri longer than ventral tentacular cirri. Dorsal and ventral tentacular cirri whitish, not papillated. One pair of short, thick ventral papillae present on segment 12 (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FDA3FE5DFD663FED" box="[599,693,474,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FD35FE5DFD363FEC" box="[705,741,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6B</figureCitation>
). Ventral segmental lamellae near ventral bases of neuropodia present on segments 13–18 (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FE22FE79FDE73C01" box="[470,564,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FDCBFE79FDB03C00" box="[575,611,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6B</figureCitation>
). Pygidium with a pair of pygidial cirri, long and slender (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FB1BFE79FA9E3C01" box="[1263,1357,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[151,1436,489,1773]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–D, 1 mm., E–F, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552087/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FAACFE79FAAE3C00" box="[1368,1405,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502FFFD2FF33FDA5FA5B3D45" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
Parapodia biramous (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FE43FDA5FDC03C24" box="[439,531,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-408@7.[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552089/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FDD5FDA5FD963C24" box="[545,581,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6C</figureCitation>
). Notopodia shorter than neuropodia. Notopodia with short conical acicular lobes, on elytrigerous segments, with prominent bracts enclosing notochaetae dorsally and posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FACDFDC1FA443C78" box="[1337,1431,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-408@7.[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552089/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FF63FDEDFF683C9C" box="[151,187,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6C</figureCitation>
). About 50 notochaetae in each notopodium. Notochaetae short to long, with distinct rows of spines along one side, tapering to blunt tips, unidentate (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FDA0FD09FD623CB0" box="[596,689,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-408@7.[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552089/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs 5C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FD4AFD09FD373CB0" box="[702,740,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,193,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 12–20; C, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">6D</figureCitation>
), stouter than neurochaetae. Neuropodia with subconical prechaetal lobes tapering to sharp tips; post chaetal lobes shorter, rounded. Neurochaetae of 
<specimenCount id="9D7D5BD3502FFFD2FB8EFD34FB0E3CD4" box="[1146,1245,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="generic" typeStatus="type">one type</specimenCount>
, numerous, short to long, with borders finely spinous, tips slightly hooked and finely spinous, spines long and widely spaced in subdistal region, without semi-lunar pockets (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502FFFD2FD86FD7DFD183D0C" box="[626,715,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-408@7.[151,1436,992,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Branchinotogluma sagamiensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, left side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552089/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Robust acicula in each ramum. Ventral cirri tapered, not papillated, attached on middle part of parapodia. On segment 2, ventral cirri elongated and projecting from neuropodia. Branchiae present from chaetigers 3 to 16, short, with 8–10 filaments, arborescent, two pouches per parapodium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502FFFD2FF33FCE1FA4E3D99" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,1437,870,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Pharynx with four pairs of papillae terminally and two pairs of jaws.Jaws growing inwardly, with minute denticles.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502FFFD2FF33FC0DFB663DBD" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,1205,906,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502FFFD2FF33FC0DFEEB3DBD" bold="true" box="[199,312,906,932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Variation</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus id="54C02EF8502FFFD2FEB2FC0CFE603DBC" box="[326,435,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Paratypes</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4C833DBF502FFFD2FE4EFC0CFE283DBC" box="[442,507,907,933]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502FFFD2FDB6FC0DFD503DBC" box="[578,643,906,933]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide. Ventral papillae absent in female specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502FFFD2FF33FC29FB183DD1" box="[199,1227,942,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502FFFD2FF33FC29FB183DD1" blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,1227,942,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502FFFD2FF33FC29FE813DD1" bold="true" box="[199,338,942,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Etymology:</emphasis>
Named after the 
<typeStatus id="54C02EF8502FFFD2FDE0FC28FD973DD0" box="[532,580,943,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
locality (Sagami Bay). The specific name is an adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
