<subSubSection id="C361C3D15021FFDCFF33FF11FA5D3EA8" box="[199,1422,150,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A5021FFDCFF33FF11FA5D3EA8" blockId="9.[151,1436,150,456]" box="[199,1422,150,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFF33FF11FE8A3EA9" bold="true" box="[199,345,150,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Distribution</emphasis>
: Hydrocarbon seep area, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF5021FFDCFD8CFF10FD123EA8" box="[632,705,151,177]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.67" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="867.0">867 m</quantity>
, Off Hatsushima, Sagami Bay, 
<collectingCountry id="F36CD0CA5021FFDCFBD5FF10FBB73EA8" box="[1057,1124,151,177]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Northwest Pacific Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D15021FFDCFF33FF3EFBF63FD1" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A5021FFDCFF33FF3EFBF63FD1" blockId="9.[151,1436,150,456]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFF33FF3EFEE73ECA" bold="true" box="[199,308,185,211]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
: This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD95021FFDCFD71FF3EFAC53ECD" authority="(Miura &amp; Desbruyeres, 1995)" baseAuthorityName="Miura &amp; Desbruyeres" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[645,1302,185,212]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="trifurcus">
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFD71FF3EFC6D3ECA" box="[645,958,185,211]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Branchinotogluma trifurcus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB5021FFDCFC39FF3EFADD3ECD" author="Miura, T. &amp; Desbruyeres, D." box="[973,1294,185,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" pagination="583 - 595" refId="ref6231" refString="Miura, T. &amp; Desbruyeres, D. (1995) Two new species of Opisthotrochopodus (Polychaeta: Polynoidae: Branchinotogluminae) from the Lau and North Fiji Bac arc basins, southwestern Pacific Ocean. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 108, 583 - 595." type="journal article" year="1995">Miura &amp; Desbruyères, 1995</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having a cylindrical anterior lobe, absence of conical frontal filaments, and presence of short ventral papillae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB5021FFDCFB0AFF5BFEE83F00" author="Miura, T. &amp; Desbruyeres, D." pageId="9" pageNumber="26" pagination="583 - 595" refId="ref6231" refString="Miura, T. &amp; Desbruyeres, D. (1995) Two new species of Opisthotrochopodus (Polychaeta: Polynoidae: Branchinotogluminae) from the Lau and North Fiji Bac arc basins, southwestern Pacific Ocean. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 108, 583 - 595." type="journal article" year="1995">Miura &amp; Desbruyères 1995</bibRefCitation>
). The new species can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD95021FFDCFCCAFF78FC6E3F00" baseAuthorityName="Miura &amp; Desbruyeres" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[830,957,255,281]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="trifurcus">
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFCCAFF78FC6E3F00" box="[830,957,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">B. trifurcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following features: 
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFB04FF78FB2B3F01" box="[1264,1272,255,280]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">i</emphasis>
) 20 segments; 
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFF63FEA5FF743F22" box="[151,167,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">ii</emphasis>
) dorsal tentacular cirri longer than ventral tentacular cirri; 
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFCB9FEA5FCB73F22" box="[845,868,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">iii</emphasis>
) ventral segmental lamellae near ventral bases of neuropodia present on segments 13–18; 
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFDAFFEC2FDBC3F47" box="[603,623,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">iv</emphasis>
) median antenna thin. This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD95021FFDCFB79FEC3FA8C3F47" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1985" box="[1165,1375,324,350]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFB79FEC3FA8C3F47" box="[1165,1375,324,350]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Branchinotogluma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a hydrocarbon seep in 
<collectingCountry id="F36CD0CA5021FFDCFE63FEE0FE093F98" box="[407,474,359,385]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Although categorized as a seep due to the typically cool temperature, the geofluid of the Off Hatsushima seep is probably hydrothermal in origin, since fluids as high as 11.6°C have been measured and the temperature of the end-member is said to be 34–54 °C (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB5021FFDCFCDAFE2AFBCA3FD1" author="Tsunogai, U. &amp; Ishibashi, J. &amp; Wakita, H. &amp; Gamo, T. &amp; Masuzawa, T. &amp; Nakatsuka, T. &amp; Nojiri, Y. &amp; Nakamura, T." box="[814,1049,429,456]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" pagination="157 - 168" refId="ref6810" refString="Tsunogai, U., Ishibashi, J., Wakita, H., Gamo, T., Masuzawa, T., Nakatsuka, T., Nojiri, Y. &amp; Nakamura, T. (1996) Fresh water seepage and pore water recycling on the seafloor: Sagami Trough subductione zone, Japan. Earth and Planetary Science Letters, 138, 157 - 168. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0012 - 821 X (95) 00228 - 5" type="journal article" year="1996">
Tsunogai 
<emphasis id="B90F4C485021FFDCFC6AFE29FC053FDE" box="[926,982,429,455]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
